SUMMARY:Deadline: PRS Foundation: Open Fund for Music Creators (Autumn 2026
  Round)
DESCRIPTION:The PRS Foundation Open Fund for Music Creators supports songwr
 iters\, composers\, artists\, bands and producers of any genre to create\,
  release and share new music\, including recordings\, performances\, touri
 ng and creative development. Grants are up to GBP 5\,000. Open to UK-based
  music creators aged 18 or over with at least an 18-month track record\, w
 ho are not full-time students. This Autumn round opens 17 August 2026 with
  a deadline of 7 September 2026. NOTE: research-sourced\; confirm current 
 figures and round dates on the PRS Foundation site before applying.\n\nOrg
 anisation: PRS Foundation\nLocation: United Kingdom. UK-based music creato
 rs aged 18 or over with an 18-month track record\; not full-time students.
 \nAward: Up to GBP 5\,000 for projects involving the creation\, performanc
 e and promotion of new music. No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based
 .\n\nMore: https://prsfoundation.com/the-open-fund-for-music-creators-guid
 ance-faqs/
URL:https://prsfoundation.com/the-open-fund-for-music-creators-guidance-faq
 s/
LOCATION:United Kingdom. UK-based music creators aged 18 or over with an 18
 -month track record\; not full-time students.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
